== ''''''Plunder'''''' ==

Pronunciation: 'pl&n-d&r
1 a : to take the goods of by force (as in war) : PILLAGE, SACK <invaders plundered the town> b : to take by force or wrongfully : STEAL, LOOT
2 : to make extensive use of as if by plundering : use or use up wrongfully <plunder the land>
intransitive senses : to commit robbery or looting